# Euler Problem: Generate the Theoretical Spectrum of a Linear Peptide

## Problem Description

The theoretical spectrum of a linear peptide is the multiset of masses of all subpeptides of the peptide, including the empty subpeptide and the entire peptide itself. Given a linear peptide, we need to compute all possible subpeptide masses.

  "Generate the theoretical spectrum of a linear peptide.
   Returns a list of all subpeptide masses sorted in ascending order."
  (let ((mass-table (make-mass-table))
        (spectrum '()))
    ;; Generate all subpeptides and their masses
    (loop for i from 0 below (length peptide) do
      (loop for j from (1+ i) to (length peptide) do
        (let ((subpeptide (subseq peptide i j))
              (mass 0))
          ;; Calculate mass of subpeptide
          (loop for aa across subpeptide do
            (incf mass (gethash aa mass-table 0)))
          ;; Add mass to spectrum
          (push mass spectrum))))
    ;; Add mass of entire peptide

      (loop for aa across peptide do
        (incf total-mass (gethash aa mass-table 0)))
      (push total-mass spectrum))
    ;; Add mass of empty subpeptide (0)
    (push 0 spectrum)
    ;; Sort and return spectrum
    (sort spectrum '<)))
